<TEXT>
hundreds of people turned out sunday for 
the wake of a black teenager whose shooting by a white policeman 
sparked a rampage last week in a suburban town 
my son my son they shot him in the back 16yearold 
phillip pannells weeping father phillip sr said as he was led 
out of the community baptist church 
a candlelight vigil the day after pannell was shot tuesday in 
teaneck turned violent as scores of black youths rampaged and 
looted businesses 
it had been feared more violence would break out sunday but 
police said both teaneck and englewood were calm 
black muslim leader louis farrakhan attended the wake 
a funeral service for pannell was set for monday at the same 
church 
pannell was shot by teaneck police officer gary spath who was 
responding to an anonymous tip that a teenager was brandishing a 
gun 
spath has since been suspended with pay and wayne blanco the 
officer who responded with spath has been temporarily relieved of 
his duties acting bergen county prosecutor john holl said 
an autopsy showed that pannell was shot once in the back an 
investigation showed that spaths 38caliber service revolver had 
been fired twice and that blancos revolver was not fired 
a grand jury is to begin considering the case tuesday 
