<TEXT>
about 60 passengers and crew members on a 
usair flight were forced to evacuate on emergency chutes sunday 
after a flight attendant smelled smoke in the rear of the cabin an 
airline spokesman said 
flight 2370 from louisville to the greater pittsburgh 
international airport with 54 passengers and six or seven crew 
members aboard landed in pittsburgh around 330 pm said usair 
spokesman john bronson 
a woman suffered a scraped knee when left the plane on a chute 
bronson said 
maintenance workers later found that the smell came from burnt 
oil that leaked from a malfunctioning rotary shaft of an air 
conditioning unit the spokesman said 
it was a relatively minor problem bronson said they 
erred on the side of caution 
