<TEXT>
police on sunday were investigating whether a 
cab driver found shot to death in his taxi was the fourth victim of 
a serial killer 
rafael montes de oca 38 was found in his car at 1155 pm 
saturday in the bronx police said he was shot in the head at 
close range as were three other private carservice drivers killed 
in the bronx since march 7 
police had not ruled out that the killer believed responsible 
for the previous three slayings may have struck again said police 
spokesman hugh barry 
but police at the 48th precinct which is investigating the 
latest killing were leaning against connecting it to the others 
there are certain consistencies in the other cases which are 
not present in this one said lt james malvey the precinct 
commander we became convinced there is no connection 
a detective in the precinct said investigators were treating the 
latest slaying as a separate incident but theyre not ruling a 
connection out definitely its too soon the detective spoke on 
condition of anonymity 
a task force of more than 30 officers formed last week to probe 
the homicides was investigating the montes de oca killing barry 
said 
it was not immediately determined if any money had been stolen 
before the killing 
a fifth cab driver dennis forbes was shot during a robbery 
wednesday and died the next day but his death was not believed to 
be related to the others detectives said montes de oca and the 
other three slain drivers had all received calls to pick up 
passengers while forbes picked up a passenger on the street 
montes de oca had worked for seaman car services of manhattan 
for about two years 
he had gone to a bronx address to pick up a passenger said 
leslie rivera a seaman dispatcher we didnt hear from him 
since she said we were notified by another driver that he was 
shot 
she said montes de oca had a pregnant wife and four children 
everybody here is devastated said raul morel another 
dispatcher 
like other cab companies seaman has lost taxi drivers because 
of fear instilled by the string of killings ten to 15 percent of 
its 350 drivers no longer work at night rivera said 
everybody takes extra measures but what can you do morel 
said the only precaution that we take is when you see the 
people if you see a person that you dont like you dont take 
them 
mayor david dinkins offered a 10000 reward on thursday for 
information leading to the killer or killers 
the guardian angels meanwhile announced that one member of the 
group would begin riding with each driver for two car services on 
their overnight runs sunday night 
we look upon these car services as the lifeline in these 
communities said lisa sliwa of the angels a volunteer group 
known for its red berets and controversial crimefighting tactics 
without them theres no way for people like nurses who work late 
to get around 
