of the philippine constabulary was charged with commandeering two 
passenger buses and reinforcing rebel troops during the coup 
attempt 
officials said dioneda jumped from a window when troops arrived 
but was captured after a brief chase 
he is among the more than 2200 mutineers in military custody 
eightyone officers have been charged in the december coup 
in another development a separate renegade group on saturday 
threatened to attack suspected british mercenaries allegedly 
training mrs aquinos security forces 
the warning by the young officers union came in an open letter 
for the british embassy dated friday copies were sent to news 
agencies 
