<TEXT>
a driver for a private car service was fatally 
shot at close range in the bronx borough of new york late saturday 
the fifth such killing in five weeks police said 
police were investigating whether the driver was the victim of 
the same robber believed responsible for three of the earlier 
slayings 
the driver was found dead in his car at 1155 pm in the 
fordham section of the bronx said sgt nick vreeland a police 
spokesman 
the victim rafael montes de oca 38 of the bronx was shot in 
the head at close range vreeland said he would not immediately 
say how many times the victim had been shot 
the driver who worked for seaman car services in manhattan had 
picked up a passenger who called for a ride said leslie rivera a 
seaman dispatcher 
we didnt hear from him since she said we were notified 
by another driver that he was shot 
rivera described the victim as a good family man and a good 
fellow worker he had four children and his wife is pregnant 
she added 
carservice drivers were shot to death in the bronx on march 7 
march 14 and april 9th after receiving calls to pick up a 
passenger in the early morning hours 
investigators believe the three were the victims of the same 
person because the drivers were all shot many times in the face and 
neck with a 22 caliber gun each had been robbed of between 50 
and 150 
a fourth driver was shot in the head wednesday and died the next 
day but detectives believe that killing was unrelated to the other 
three because the victim had picked up a passenger who flagged him 
down on the street and because witnesses saw two people running 
from the car 
like other cab companies seaman has lost taxi drivers to fear 
instilled by the string of killings ten to fifteen percent of its 
350 drivers are no longer working at night rivera said 
mayor david dinkins offered a 10000 reward thursday for 
information leading to the killer or killers of the drivers police 
commissioner lee brown formed a task force of more than 30 officers 
to focus on the homicides 
