<TEXT>
france marked the 10th anniversary of jeanpaul 
sartres death sunday with a mixture of praise and suggestions from 
intellectuals that many of his leftist political ideas would be out 
of place in todays world 
in commemorative newspaper and magazine articles this week 
sartre was saluted as one of frances outstanding philosophers and 
writers 
yet the praise generally was mixed with comments that sartres 
leftist sympathies and belief that marxism could be molded into a 
viable ideology has been overtaken by recent political events 
if sartre came back he wouldnt find the world had simply 
changed its an entirely different universe he would discover 
without the iron curtain or peoples republics with communism in 
agony wrote liberation the leftist newspaper which sartre 
founded in the early 1970s 
liberations robert maggiori wrote that sartres political work 
has become a mirror reflecting an epoch that doesnt exist any 
more in a language that isnt spoken any more a broken mirror in 
which nothing can be recognized 
sartre who would have been 85 on sunday openly supported the 
communist party through the 1930s he later denounced stalins 
brutal purges and the soviets crushing of the hungarian uprising 
in 1956 but even in subsequent years he balked at renouncing 
communist theory or leftwing terrorists despite his eloquent 
advocacy of individual freedom 
the philosopher of liberty he blindly justified the worst 
despotisms of his century and even affirmed i have fought all my 
life for a society in which i would not want to live wrote 
essayist pascal brickner this week in express magazine 
it is alas the worst of sartre that lives today the 
critical spirit gone astray the habit of taking up a cause 
without considering it brickner wrote he wasted a large part 
of his talent on the esthetics of violence and revolution 
sartre was born in paris on june 21 1905 and was raised by his 
mother alone after his father died when he was a year old 
he taught school studied philosophy began his decadeslong 
romance with the writer simone de beauvoir was drafted into the 
army and was a german prisoner of war in 194041 before being 
freed 
some of his greatest works his plays the flies and no 
exit and his first major treatise on existentialism being and 
nothingness were written in paris during the war brickner 
among others questioned whether perhaps sartre had shirked his 
duty to the antinazi resistance by focusing on his work 
in 1964 sartre was awarded the nobel prize for literature but 
turned it down seeking to show his contempt for an honor he 
considered bourgeois 
four years later he supported french students during 
politically inspired riots and founded a maoistoriented 
publication called the peoples cause in 1974 he went to 
germany to visit members of the baadermeinhof terrorist group and 
described their actions as necessary to achieve a new 
organization of the masses 
but in 1975 sartre was virtually out of public view sick and 
going blind although he made a dramatic visit to israel in 1976 
he accepted an honorary degree from hebrew university and declared 
that his support for palestinian guerrilla attacks did not mean he 
opposed israel 
