a conversation i had with him about three years ago i asked how he 
would like to be remembered and he said id like to be 
remembered as a friend a friend of the war veterans as a 
friend of the forgotten those who have no friends as one who 
supports those who are peacemakers as your friend i said 
im certain youll be remembered as a friend of hawaii 
matsunaga was known more for his easygoing manner and his warm 
treatment of constituents than his impact on legislation but when 
he cared deeply about an issue he combined skill and perseverance 
to win passage 
in 1988 he engineered passage of a 125 billion law that pays 
20000 to each surviving japaneseamerican interned in a us 
prison camp during world war ii 
