war ii had to overcome opposition to the internment law from some 
veterans and from those who objected to its cost during debate 
the senator was forced to halt his comments in midsentence while 
telling of an elderly internee killed by a guard as he went to pick 
up a softball 
i myself become overly emotional when i think about it even to 
this day he said after regaining his composure 
matsunaga lobbied for 22 years before persuading congress in 
1984 to establish a us peace institute peacemaking is as much 
an art to be learned as war was his persistent argument 
matsunaga supported a joint ussoviet exploration of mars 
sponsored a plan for an international space year in 1992 and worked 
to make his state a center for space exploration 
waihee said sunday he will be remembered most for his vision 
of peace and his faith in the human heart in his memory we will 
carry on his quest in his spirit we will strive for the highest of 
principles and the brightest of worlds 
senator matsunaga has been a steady and guiding force 
throughout hawaiis modern history sparky warmed our state and 
country with his humanitarianism 
matsunaga was first elected to the house in 1962 and the senate 
in 1976 
when he died he was the secondranking democrat on the finance 
committee and chairman of its subcommittee on taxation and debt 
management 
before going to washington matsunaga was a member of hawaiis 
territorial house from 1954 to 1959 
he was born oct 8 1916 on kauai island the son of immigrants 
from japan 
after graduating from the university of hawaii with honors in 
1941 matsunaga joined the 100th infantry battalion which later 
became part of the famed 442nd regimental combat team the go for 
broke 442nd would become the most decorated regiment in us 
history 
matsunaga was wounded twice during world war ii he was awarded 
numerous medals including the bronze star and purple heart with 
cluster 
matsunaga was a member of the class of 54 hawaii 
democrats who came to power before statehood and established a 
political dynasty that continues to this day inouye was another 
member of the class 
matsunaga is survived by a wife helene hatsumi tokunaga and 
five children 
