<TEXT>
at various times she was reported to be ready to marry actor 
john gilbert maestro leopold stokowski health food enthusiast 
gayelord hauser and director rouben mamoulian but as she had said 
early in her career marriage i have said over and over again 
that i do not know 
her career began to wane in the late 1930s but bounced back with 
the comedy ninotchka which prompted marquees across america to 
blaze garbo laughs but her next attempt at a humorous role in 
twofaced woman flopped and miss garbo announced her retirement 
in 1941 
in 1949 she went to italy to film la duchesse de langlais 
but the project was delayed and eventually fell through 
miss garbo a millionaire through many investments had no need 
to work again she never did 
although nominated four times for academy awards she didnt win 
one until 1955 a special oscar for a series of luminous and 
unforgettable performances she did not appear to collect it 
she became an american citizen in 1951 and moved her permanent 
home from hollywood to manhattan where she sometimes used the name 
harriet brown she also maintained a residence in klosters 
switzerland 
garbo watchers would wait hours outside her apartment 
hoping to catch a glimpse of her 
details of her private life rarely leaked out but in the 1940s 
she was linked with russianborn entrepreneur george schlee whose 
wife valentina designed miss garbos clothes she purchased an 
apartment in the schlees building the entrepreneur was soon 
traveling alone with miss garbo although he remained married 
the relationship lasted nearly 25 years until schlee died in 
1964 
her enduring popularity was evident when in the 1960s dozens of 
garbo festivals were held worldwide but miss garbo as always 
remained aloof 
in a rare interview in 1928 she said there are many things 
in your heart you can never tell to another person they are you 
your private joys and sorrows and you can never tell them you 
cheapen yourself the inside of yourself when you tell them 
when she saw the words in print miss garbo was furious with the 
writer i do not like your story she said 
however in 1985 sven broman a swedish magazine publisher and 
garbo biographer released details of conversations he said he had 
had the summer before with the actress 
according to broman miss garbo said she longed to return to 
sweden but feared the resulting commotion 
neighbor buttenweiser said he had known the actress for 35 
years he said he sometimes discussed world developments with 
garbo but said she wouldnt talk about her film career 
she wanted to know about germany about europe she wanted to 
know what was going on in new york said buttenweiser she was 
a very interesting person 
for most of her life the actress apparently decided to let her 
films speak for her 
the result of our life should bear witness to what we are 
what we will do what we can achieve she said as a budding 
teenage star and our work tells this best in its own language 
mine happens to be the language of the motion picture screen 
new york hospital spokesman banoff said the family had asked 
that instead of flowers donations be made to a kidney treatment 
center at the hospital 
he said he didnt know who the family members were but 
neighbors said miss garbo had a niece 
he said services would be private 
